<header>

# CUDA C++ Setup Guide

*Compile and run CUDA C++ programs using NVCC, Visual Studio, and CMake on Windows.*

</header>

---

## Requirements

Before starting, install the following:

| Software                | Purpose                          |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit     | CUDA compiler and libraries      |
| Visual Studio Community | Required MSVC compiler           |
| CMake *(optional)*      | Build system for larger projects |

### Downloads

* CUDA Toolkit
  https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads

* Visual Studio Community
  https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/vs/community/

* CMake
  https://cmake.org/download/

---

## Important

CUDA programs will NOT work correctly with:

* Dev-C++
* CodeBlocks
* GCC alone

You must use:

* `nvcc`
* Visual Studio Build Tools
* or CMake with CUDA support

---

## Step 1: Install Visual Studio

Install **Visual Studio Community Edition**.

During installation, enable:

* Desktop development with C++

---

## Step 2: Install CUDA Toolkit

Install the CUDA Toolkit after Visual Studio.

Verify installation:

```cmd
nvcc --version
```

Expected output:

```text
Cuda compilation tools, release 12.x
```

---

## Step 3: Open Developer Command Prompt

Open CMD and run:

```cmd
"C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\2022\Community\Common7\Tools\VsDevCmd.bat" -arch=x64
```

> Your Visual Studio path may be different.

This loads the MSVC compiler environment required by CUDA.

---

## Step 4: Move to Project Folder

Example:

```cmd
cd Desktop\CUDAProject
```

---

## Step 5: Compile CUDA Program

Compile using:

```cmd
nvcc main.cu -o main.exe
```

General syntax:

```cmd
nvcc {filename}.cu -o {exename}.exe
```

Example:

```cmd
nvcc vectorAdd.cu -o vectorAdd.exe
```

---

## Step 6: Run Program

```cmd
main.exe
```

---

## Using CMake (Optional)

### Example Project Structure

```text
CUDAProject/
│
├── CMakeLists.txt
└── main.cu
```

### Example CMakeLists.txt

```cmake
cmake_minimum_required(VERSION 3.18)

project(CUDAProject LANGUAGES CXX CUDA)

add_executable(main main.cu)

set_target_properties(main PROPERTIES
    CUDA_SEPARABLE_COMPILATION ON
)
```

### Build Commands

```cmd
mkdir build
cd build

cmake ..
cmake --build .
```

---

## Common Errors

| Error                  | Cause                | Solution                                      |
| ---------------------- | -------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| nvcc is not recognized | CUDA PATH missing    | Reinstall CUDA or add CUDA bin folder to PATH |
| cl.exe not found       | VS tools not loaded  | Run VsDevCmd.bat first                        |
| Unsupported compiler   | Wrong VS version     | Install supported Visual Studio               |
| .cu file not compiling | Using GCC or Dev-C++ | Use NVCC                                      |

---

## Useful Commands

| Command         | Purpose             |
| --------------- | ------------------- |
| nvcc --version  | Check CUDA compiler |
| nvidia-smi      | Check GPU drivers   |
| cmake --version | Check CMake         |
| where nvcc      | Find CUDA compiler  |

---

## Minimal Workflow

```cmd
1. Open CMD

2. Run:
"C:\Program Files\Microsoft Visual Studio\2022\Community\Common7\Tools\VsDevCmd.bat" -arch=x64

3. Go to project folder:
cd Desktop\CUDAProject

4. Compile:
nvcc main.cu -o main.exe

5. Run:
main.exe
```

